deviceType.name: deviceType
deviceType.description: This object defines the board type for the Management board in the device. (eg. IRBM, IRM). See appendix A for value.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: An ASCII name of the device that this agent manages.

deviceIPAddress.name: deviceIPAddress
deviceIPAddress.description: The Internet address of this device.

currentTime.name: currentTime
currentTime.description: The current time of day as measured by the device

currentDate.name: currentDate
currentDate.description: Character representation of the current date

mACAddress.name: mACAddress
mACAddress.description: The MAC (Ethernet) address of the MMAC. This can also be obtained from address translation MIB. The Instance Identifier for the MAC address is interface number. For the IRBM, their are 2.

deviceSlots.name: deviceSlots
deviceSlots.description: Number of available device slots in this device, including the IRM slot.

deviceOccupiedSlots.name: deviceOccupiedSlots
deviceOccupiedSlots.description: The slots that contain MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (eg. If a bit is set then that board is present. For example, a value of 3 indicates that there are boards in the IRM slot and the first MIM slot.

devicePortsOn.name: devicePortsOn
devicePortsOn.description: The number of operating ports on the device.

deviceTotalPorts.name: deviceTotalPorts
deviceTotalPorts.description: The total number of repeater ports on the MMAC.

deviceTotalPkts.name: deviceTotalPkts
deviceTotalPkts.description: The number of packets detected on all ports of this device.

deviceTotalErrors.name: deviceTotalErrors
deviceTotalErrors.description: The sum of all of the errors listed including alignment,CRC, runts, giants, and Out of window collisions.

deviceTransmitColl.name: deviceTransmitColl
deviceTransmitColl.description: The number of transmit collisions detected by this MMAC.

deviceRecColls.name: deviceRecColls
deviceRecColls.description: The number of receive collsions detected by this MMAC.

deviceAlign.name: deviceAlign
deviceAlign.description: The number of packets with alignement errors detected.

deviceCRC.name: deviceCRC
deviceCRC.description: The number of packets with bad CRC detected.

deviceRunt.name: deviceRunt
deviceRunt.description: The number of runt frames detected by this device.

deviceOOWColl.name: deviceOOWColl
deviceOOWColl.description: The number of out-of-window collisions detected by this

deviceNoResources.name: deviceNoResources
deviceNoResources.description: The number of No resource condtions detected.

deviceRecBytes.name: deviceRecBytes
deviceRecBytes.description: The number of bytes detected on the network.

deviceGiantFrames.name: deviceGiantFrames
deviceGiantFrames.description: The number of longer than 1518 bytes.

deviceRestart.name: deviceRestart
deviceRestart.description: If this object is set to 0 the device is restarted.

deviceResetCounter.name: deviceResetCounter
deviceResetCounter.description: If this object is set to 0, all of the devices Counters are reset to 0.

deviceRedundantCts.name: deviceRedundantCts
deviceRedundantCts.description: The number of redundant circuits available for use.

deviceTimeBase.name: deviceTimeBase
deviceTimeBase.description: The number of seconds used as the interval for performing all of the rate alarm checks. The minimum is 10 secs.

deviceResetRedundancy.name: deviceResetRedundancy
deviceResetRedundancy.description: Setting this object to a 1 will reset redundancy for the entire box.

deviceSrcAddrAgingTime.name: deviceSrcAddrAgingTime
deviceSrcAddrAgingTime.description: The number of minutes that a source address is not detected before it is removed from the source address table.

deviceSrcAddrTraps.name: deviceSrcAddrTraps
deviceSrcAddrTraps.description: Controls sending of source address related traps.

deviceSrcAddrLocked.name: deviceSrcAddrLocked
deviceSrcAddrLocked.description: If this is set to 2, any source addresses that are detected on station ports that are not in the table will cause the port to be turned off.

deviceEnetBoardMap.name: deviceEnetBoardMap
deviceEnetBoardMap.description: The slots that contain Ethernet MIM boards.

deviceTokenRingBoardMap.name: deviceTokenRingBoardMap
deviceTokenRingBoardMap.description: The slots that contain Token Ring MIM boards.

deviceFDDIBoardMap.name: deviceFDDIBoardMap
deviceFDDIBoardMap.description: The slots that contain FDDI MIM boards.

sourceAddrBoard.name: sourceAddrBoard
sourceAddrBoard.description: The board number of the port that the supplied source address has been found on.

sourceAddrPort.name: sourceAddrPort
sourceAddrPort.description: The port number of the port that the supplied source address has been found on.

redundancyPollInterval.name: redundancyPollInterval
redundancyPollInterval.description: The number of seconds between polls for redundancy.

redundancyTestTod.name: redundancyTestTod
redundancyTestTod.description: The time of day at which the redundant circuits should be tested.

redundancyCircuitName.name: redundancyCircuitName
redundancyCircuitName.description: The name of the indicated circuit.

redundancyRetryCount.name: redundancyRetryCount
redundancyRetryCount.description: The number of unanswered polls allowed for the indicated circuit before the current connection is declared bad.

redundancyNumBPs.name: redundancyNumBPs
redundancyNumBPs.description: The number of board/port combinations associated with the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitBoards.name: redundancyCircuitBoards
redundancyCircuitBoards.description: The boards associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index.

redundancyCircuitPort.name: redundancyCircuitPort
redundancyCircuitPort.description: The ports associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index.

redundancyCircuitTypes.name: redundancyCircuitTypes
redundancyCircuitTypes.description: The type of each port associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index.

redundancyCircuitNumAddr.name: redundancyCircuitNumAddr
redundancyCircuitNumAddr.description: The number of addresses associated with the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd
redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd.description: Adds the ethernet address to the polling list for the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel
redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel.description: Removes the ethernet address from the polling list for the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp
redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp.description: The ethernet addresses associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index.

redundancyCircuitEnable.name: redundancyCircuitEnable
redundancyCircuitEnable.description: Enables and disables the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitReset.name: redundancyCircuitReset
redundancyCircuitReset.description: Reset the indicated circuit. Return all of the associated board and ports to NOT-USED, remove associated addresses from the polling list, reset the circuit name and retry count to default values .

devTrafficEnable.name: devTrafficEnable
devTrafficEnable.description: Enable the sending of device level traffic traps.

devTrafficThreshold.name: devTrafficThreshold
devTrafficThreshold.description: The threshold of packets within the devicetimebase that will cause a traffic alarm.

devCollsEnable.name: devCollsEnable
devCollsEnable.description: Enable the sending of device level collsion alarms.

devCollsThreshold.name: devCollsThreshold
devCollsThreshold.description: This object represents the number of collisions per good packet measured by the device that will generate an alarm. valid values are 1 to 15

devErrorEnable.name: devErrorEnable
devErrorEnable.description: Enable the sending of device level error alarms.

devErrorThreshold.name: devErrorThreshold
devErrorThreshold.description: This object represents the percentage of errors per good packet that will generate an alarm.

devErrorSource.name: devErrorSource
devErrorSource.description: The type of error used for the error alarm.

bdTrafficEnable.name: bdTrafficEnable
bdTrafficEnable.description: Enable the sending of board level traffic traps for this board.

bdTrafficThreshold.name: bdTrafficThreshold
bdTrafficThreshold.description: The threshold of packets within the Devicetimebase that will cause a traffic alarm.

bdCollsEnable.name: bdCollsEnable
bdCollsEnable.description: Enable the sending of board level collsion alarms.

bdCollsThreshold.name: bdCollsThreshold
bdCollsThreshold.description: This object represents the number of collisions per good packet measured by the board that will generate an alarm. valid values are 1 to 15

bdErrorEnable.name: bdErrorEnable
bdErrorEnable.description: Enable the sending of board level error alarms.

bdErrorThreshold.name: bdErrorThreshold
bdErrorThreshold.description: This object represents the percentage of errors per good packet that will generate an alarm.

bdErrorSource.name: bdErrorSource
bdErrorSource.description: The type of error used for the error alarm.

portTrafficEnable.name: portTrafficEnable
portTrafficEnable.description: Enable the sending of port level traffic traps for this port.

portTrafficThreshold.name: portTrafficThreshold
portTrafficThreshold.description: The threshold of packets within the Devicetimebase that will cause a traffic alarm.

portCollsEnable.name: portCollsEnable
portCollsEnable.description: Enable the sending of port level collsion alarms.

portCollsThreshold.name: portCollsThreshold
portCollsThreshold.description: This object represents the number of collisions per good packet measured by the port that will generate an alarm.

portErrorEnable.name: portErrorEnable
portErrorEnable.description: Enable the sending of port level error alarms.

portErrorThreshold.name: portErrorThreshold
portErrorThreshold.description: This object represents the percentage of errors per good packet that will generate an alarm.

portErrorSource.name: portErrorSource
portErrorSource.description: The type of error used for the error alarm.

deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn.name: deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn
deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn.description: The number of Token Ring Ports (i.e. station, Ring In and Ring Out ports) enabled on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts
deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts.description: The total number of Token Ring Ports (i.e. station, Ring In and Ring Out ports) on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn.description: The total number of Ring In and Ring Out ports (active) enabled on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts.description: The total number of Ring In and Ring Out ports on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings.description: The total number of (Token Ring) rings formed on this device.

boardIndex.name: boardIndex
boardIndex.description: The slot number of this board.

boardName.name: boardName
boardName.description: The name of the board. This field will only contain printable ASCII characters.

boardType.name: boardType
boardType.description: The type of the MIM. (eg. FOT, TPT, etc). See appendix A for encoding.

boardTotalPorts.name: boardTotalPorts
boardTotalPorts.description: Total number of ports supported on this board.

boardSTATUS.name: boardSTATUS
boardSTATUS.description: The administrative status of this MIM.

boardPortsOn.name: boardPortsOn
boardPortsOn.description: The number of operating ports on the board.

boardTotalPkts.name: boardTotalPkts
boardTotalPkts.description: The total number of packets this board has seen since the last reset.

boardErrorPkts.name: boardErrorPkts
boardErrorPkts.description: The number of packets that have experienced an error. VAlid only on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

boardTransColl.name: boardTransColl
boardTransColl.description: The number of transmit collisions this board has detected.

boardRecColl.name: boardRecColl
boardRecColl.description: The number of Receive mode collisions this board has detected.

boardAlign.name: boardAlign
boardAlign.description: The number of mis-aligned frames this board has detected. Only valid for the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

boardCRC.name: boardCRC
boardCRC.description: The number of packets with bad CRC detected. Only valid on IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

boardRunt.name: boardRunt
boardRunt.description: The number of runt frames detected by this board. Valid fr the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC only.

boardOOWColl.name: boardOOWColl
boardOOWColl.description: The number of out-of-window collisions detected by this board. Only valid on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

boardNoResources.name: boardNoResources
boardNoResources.description: The number of times The no resources condition was detected for this board.

boardRecBytes.name: boardRecBytes
boardRecBytes.description: The number of bytes detected on the network. Valid only on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

boardGiants.name: boardGiants
boardGiants.description: The number of packets longer than 1518 bytes detected on this board.

boardTotalRingPorts.name: boardTotalRingPorts
boardTotalRingPorts.description: The total number of ring ports on this board. Currently, zero or two.

boardTotalStationPorts.name: boardTotalStationPorts
boardTotalStationPorts.description: The total number of station ports on this board.

boardModeStatus.name: boardModeStatus
boardModeStatus.description: The board is configured for 2 == Auto Mode or 1 == Management Mode

boardTotalRingPortsOn.name: boardTotalRingPortsOn
boardTotalRingPortsOn.description: The number of enabled ring ports on this board.

boardTotalStationPortsOn.name: boardTotalStationPortsOn
boardTotalStationPortsOn.description: The number of enabled station ports on this board.

boardRingSpeedFault.name: boardRingSpeedFault
boardRingSpeedFault.description: Data speed of station mismatches configuration speed of board. board is automatically bypassed.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: The slot number of this port.

portMediaType.name: portMediaType
portMediaType.description: The type of the port. (eg. FOT, TPT, etc). See appendix A for values.

portAdminState.name: portAdminState
portAdminState.description: The administrative status of this port.

portSourceAddr.name: portSourceAddr
portSourceAddr.description: A source address that has been seen on this port.

portTopologyType.name: portTopologyType
portTopologyType.description: The topological type of the port. { Station(1) Link(2) }

portLinkStatus.name: portLinkStatus
portLinkStatus.description: The state of the link signal for this port

portTotalPkts.name: portTotalPkts
portTotalPkts.description: The total number of packets this port has seen since the last reset.

portErrorPkts.name: portErrorPkts
portErrorPkts.description: The number of packets that have experienced an error. Valid only on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC

portXmitColls.name: portXmitColls
portXmitColls.description: The number of Transmit mode collisions this port has detected. Only valid on IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portRecColls.name: portRecColls
portRecColls.description: The number of Receive mode collisions this port has detected. Only valid on IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portAlign.name: portAlign
portAlign.description: The number of mis-aligned frames this port has detected. Only valid for the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portCRC.name: portCRC
portCRC.description: The number of packets with bad CRC detected. Only valid on IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portRunt.name: portRunt
portRunt.description: The number of runt frames detected by this port. Valid for the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC only.

portOOWColl.name: portOOWColl
portOOWColl.description: The number of out-of-window collisions detected by this port. Only valid on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portNoResorces.name: portNoResorces
portNoResorces.description: The number of times the no resource condition is detected on this port.

portRecBytes.name: portRecBytes
portRecBytes.description: The number of bytes detected on the network. Valid only on the IRBM, IRM2, and MiniMMAC.

portGiants.name: portGiants
portGiants.description: The number of frames longer than 1518 bytes detected on this port.

portRedundCrt.name: portRedundCrt
portRedundCrt.description: The redundant circuit with which this port is associated.

portRedundType.name: portRedundType
portRedundType.description: The type of port this port is in the redundant circuit.

portRedundStatus.name: portRedundStatus
portRedundStatus.description: The current state of this port is in the redundant circuit.

portForceLinkType.name: portForceLinkType
portForceLinkType.description: This variable forces a port to be a link port.

stationPortLinkStatus.name: stationPortLinkStatus
stationPortLinkStatus.description: When station is supplying phantom current the Link Signal is active. When there is no phantom current the Link Signal is inactive.

stationPortLinkStateTime.name: stationPortLinkStateTime
stationPortLinkStateTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) elapsed since the station port last changed state.

ringPortLinkStateTime.name: ringPortLinkStateTime
ringPortLinkStateTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) elapsed since ring port last changed state.

iRBMRevision.name: iRBMRevision
iRBMRevision.description: The revision of the IRBM board

iRBMPortAssociation.name: iRBMPortAssociation
iRBMPortAssociation.description: Controls how front panel ports are associated with the bridge or the repeater. The valid values are: Value AUI Port Fiber Port 0 Bridge Redundant 1 Redundant Bridge 2 Bridge Repeater 3 Repeater Bridge 4 Redundant Repeater 5 Repeater Redundant Note: only values 0 and 1 are valid for rev 2 boards and before.

fnbConnectedLeft.name: fnbConnectedLeft
fnbConnectedLeft.description: The Connected Left board (board n + 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed read ONLY).

fnbConnectedRight.name: fnbConnectedRight
fnbConnectedRight.description: The Connected Right board (board n - 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write ). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed read ONLY).

bdgdeviceDisableBdg.name: bdgdeviceDisableBdg
bdgdeviceDisableBdg.description: Indicates if the bridge will be disabled.

bdgdeviceRestoreSettings.name: bdgdeviceRestoreSettings
bdgdeviceRestoreSettings.description: Restore the following settings to their default values: Bridge Name to ETHERNET_BRIDGE, Location to LOCAL, Port 1 Name to PORT_1, Port 2 Name to PORT_2, Port 1 Network Name to LAN_1, Port 2 Network Name to LAN_2, Ageing Time for Acquired Database to 300 seconds, Erase the acquired database, Erase the permanent database, Place sixteen default multicast addresses into the permanent and acquired databases, Type of Spanning Tree to 802.1, Type of Filtering to IEEE 802.1, Bridge Max Age to 20 seconds, Bridge Forward Delay to 15 seconds, Bridge Hello Time to 2 seconds, Bridge Priority to 8000, Port 1 Priority to 80, Port 2 Priority to 80, Port 1 Path Cost to 100, Port 2 Path Cost to 100, Restart the bridge.

bdgdeviceBdgName.name: bdgdeviceBdgName
bdgdeviceBdgName.description: The user-defined name (up to 32 characters long) of the bridge. The default bridge name is ETHERNET_BRIDGE.

bdgdeviceNumPorts.name: bdgdeviceNumPorts
bdgdeviceNumPorts.description: The number of ports present on the bridge.

bdgdeviceType.name: bdgdeviceType
bdgdeviceType.description: The type of bridge, NB25E, IRBM, or NB20E.

bdgdeviceVersion.name: bdgdeviceVersion
bdgdeviceVersion.description: The release version of the firmware installed in the bridge.

bdgdeviceLocation.name: bdgdeviceLocation
bdgdeviceLocation.description: The user-defined name to indicate the location of the bridge on the network. The default location name is LOCAL.

bdgdeviceStatus.name: bdgdeviceStatus
bdgdeviceStatus.description: The status of the bridge, ON-LINE, STAND BY or DISABLED.

bdgdeviceRestartBdg.name: bdgdeviceRestartBdg
bdgdeviceRestartBdg.description: Force the bridge to undergo a software reset.

bdgdeviceFrFwd.name: bdgdeviceFrFwd
bdgdeviceFrFwd.description: The number of frames forwarded by the bridge.

bdgdeviceFrRx.name: bdgdeviceFrRx
bdgdeviceFrRx.description: The number of frames received by the bridge.

bdgdeviceFrFlt.name: bdgdeviceFrFlt
bdgdeviceFrFlt.description: The number of frames filtered by the bridge.

bdgdeviceErr.name: bdgdeviceErr
bdgdeviceErr.description: The total number of network errors that have occurred.

bdgdeviceSwitchSetting.name: bdgdeviceSwitchSetting
bdgdeviceSwitchSetting.description: Indicates the current switch settings read from the bridge hardware.

bdgdeviceNumRestarts.name: bdgdeviceNumRestarts
bdgdeviceNumRestarts.description: The number of times the bridge has been powered up or restarted.

bdgdeviceTypeFiltering.name: bdgdeviceTypeFiltering
bdgdeviceTypeFiltering.description: The type of filtering to be performed by the bridge. The default is IEEE 802.1.

bdgdeviceSTAProtocol.name: bdgdeviceSTAProtocol
bdgdeviceSTAProtocol.description: The spanning tree algorithm under which the bridge is operating. The selections are as follows: - IEEE 802.1 compliant spanning tree algorithm environment (802.1) - DEC LAN Bridge 100 environment (DEC) - Without the spanning tree algorithm enabled (NONE) The default is 802.1.

bdgdeviceBridgeID.name: bdgdeviceBridgeID
bdgdeviceBridgeID.description: The unique identifier of the bridge. The first two bytes of the identifier are the bridge priority and the last six bytes are the Ethernet address.

bdgdeviceTopChgCnt.name: bdgdeviceTopChgCnt
bdgdeviceTopChgCnt.description: The number of times the bridge's Topology Change Flag has been changed since the bridge was powered up or initialized.

bdgdeviceRootCost.name: bdgdeviceRootCost
bdgdeviceRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root from this bridge.

bdgdeviceRootPort.name: bdgdeviceRootPort
bdgdeviceRootPort.description: The port identifier for the port which offers the lowest cost path to the root, i.e. that port for which the sum of the values of the designated cost and path cost parameters held for the port is lowest.

bdgdeviceHelloTime.name: bdgdeviceHelloTime
bdgdeviceHelloTime.description: The time interval between the transmission of Configuration BPDU's by a bridge which is attempting to become the root or is the root.

bdgdeviceBdgMaxAge.name: bdgdeviceBdgMaxAge
bdgdeviceBdgMaxAge.description: The value of the Max Age parameter when the bridge is the root or is attempting to become the root. A time of 6 to 40 seconds is allowed. The default is 20 seconds.

bdgdeviceBdgFwdDly.name: bdgdeviceBdgFwdDly
bdgdeviceBdgFwdDly.description: The value of the forward delay parameter when the bridge is the root or is attempting to become the root. A time of 4 to 30 seconds is allowed.

bdgdeviceTimeTopChg.name: bdgdeviceTimeTopChg
bdgdeviceTimeTopChg.description: The time in seconds that has elapsed since the bridge's Topology Change Flag last recorded the value of a topology change.

bdgdeviceTopChg.name: bdgdeviceTopChg
bdgdeviceTopChg.description: Indicates if a bridge topology change is in progress.

bdgdeviceDesigRoot.name: bdgdeviceDesigRoot
bdgdeviceDesigRoot.description: The unique identifier of the bridge recorded as the root.

bdgdeviceMaxAge.name: bdgdeviceMaxAge
bdgdeviceMaxAge.description: The maximum age of received protocol information before it is discarded.

bdgdeviceHoldTime.name: bdgdeviceHoldTime
bdgdeviceHoldTime.description: The minimum time period elapsing between the transmission of configuration BPDU's through a given bridge port.

bdgdeviceFwdDly.name: bdgdeviceFwdDly
bdgdeviceFwdDly.description: The time spent in the listening state while moving from the blocking state to the learning state, or the time spent in the learning state while moving from the listening state to the forwarding state.

bdgdeviceBdgHello.name: bdgdeviceBdgHello
bdgdeviceBdgHello.description: The value of the Hello Time parameter when the bridge is the root or is attempting to become the root. A time of 1 to 10 seconds is allowed. The default is 2 seconds.

bdgdeviceBdgPriority.name: bdgdeviceBdgPriority
bdgdeviceBdgPriority.description: The part of the bridge address that contains the identifier used in the spanning tree for priority comparisons. Allowed range is 0 through FFFF. The default is 8000.

bdgdeviceUptime.name: bdgdeviceUptime
bdgdeviceUptime.description: The time, in seconds, that has elapsed since the bridge was last reset or initialized.

bdgdeviceTrapType.name: bdgdeviceTrapType
bdgdeviceTrapType.description: Contains the object identifier of the first VarBinding in the last trap generated by the bridge.

bdgPortAddress.name: bdgPortAddress
bdgPortAddress.description: The Ethernet address of the port.

bdgPortName.name: bdgPortName
bdgPortName.description: The user-defined name assigned to the port. The default port 1 name is PORT_1 and the default Port 2 name is PORT_2.

bdgPortType.name: bdgPortType
bdgPortType.description: The IEEE specification the port meets, e.g. 802.3.

bdgPortStatus.name: bdgPortStatus
bdgPortStatus.description: The status in which the port is operating. The status messages for Ports 1 and 2 are: OFF - The port is off, due to a failed network interface chip associated with that port. OK/SQE ON - The port is communicating with the network and the transceiver making the connection to the network has SQE enabled. OK/SQE OFF - The port is communicating with the network and the transceiver making the connection to the network has SQE disabled. CARRIER LOST - Communication with the network has not been established or has been lost.

bdgPortNetName.name: bdgPortNetName
bdgPortNetName.description: The user-defined name assigned to a network segment connected to the port. The default network name for Port 1 is LAN_1 and the default network name for Port 2 is LAN_2.

bdgPortFrRx.name: bdgPortFrRx
bdgPortFrRx.description: The number of frames received at the specified port.

bdgPortDisInb.name: bdgPortDisInb
bdgPortDisInb.description: The total number of valid frames that were received at the port but then discarded by the bridge in the forwarding process.

bdgPortFwdOutb.name: bdgPortFwdOutb
bdgPortFwdOutb.description: The number of frames forwarded successfully to the appropriate port.

bdgPortDisLOB.name: bdgPortDisLOB
bdgPortDisLOB.description: The number of packets that were discarded by the bridge because of a lack of buffer space to maintain the data.

bdgPortDisTDE.name: bdgPortDisTDE
bdgPortDisTDE.description: The number of frames that were intended for forwarding but were discarded when the maximum time period set for transmission was exceeded before forwarding was possible.

bdgPortDisErr.name: bdgPortDisErr
bdgPortDisErr.description: The number of frames that could not be transmitted because the frame was too large for the attached network (1526 bytes, including preamble, for 802.3 networks).

bdgPortColl.name: bdgPortColl
bdgPortColl.description: The number of collisions that have occurred on the network at the specified port.

bdgPortTxAbrt.name: bdgPortTxAbrt
bdgPortTxAbrt.description: The number of transmissions that have been aborted due to excessive collisions (over 16 attempts to transmit the same packet).

bdgPortOowColl.name: bdgPortOowColl
bdgPortOowColl.description: The number of collisions out of the standard collision window (51.2 uS). This indicates a network problem.

bdgPortCRCErr.name: bdgPortCRCErr
bdgPortCRCErr.description: The number of packets detected with Cyclical Redundancy Check failures.

bdgPortFrAlErr.name: bdgPortFrAlErr
bdgPortFrAlErr.description: The number of errors due to misaligned packets.

bdgPortPriority.name: bdgPortPriority
bdgPortPriority.description: The part of the port identifier which is used with the spanning tree algorithm when determining which port in a LAN segment has priority. The default is 80.

bdgPortState.name: bdgPortState
bdgPortState.description: The current state of the port, DISABLED, LISTENING, LEARNING, FORWARDING or BLOCKING.

bdgPortPathCost.name: bdgPortPathCost
bdgPortPathCost.description: The contributory cost of the applicable port to the overall cost of the path when the specified port is the root port. Allowable range is 1 to 65535. The default is 100.

bdgPortDesigCost.name: bdgPortDesigCost
bdgPortDesigCost.description: The cost of the path of this port to the root bridge on the network.

bdgPortDesigBrdg.name: bdgPortDesigBrdg
bdgPortDesigBrdg.description: The network address of the bridge that is assumed to be the root bridge on the network.

bdgPortDesigPort.name: bdgPortDesigPort
bdgPortDesigPort.description: The port identifier of the bridge port believed to be the designated port for the LAN associated with the port.

bdgPortTopChgAck.name: bdgPortTopChgAck
bdgPortTopChgAck.description: The value of the topology change acknowledgement flag in the next configuration BPDU to be transmitted on the associated port.

bdgPortDesigRoot.name: bdgPortDesigRoot
bdgPortDesigRoot.description: The unique bridge identifier of the bridge that is assumed to be the root bridge on the network.

bdgPortRuntPackets.name: bdgPortRuntPackets
bdgPortRuntPackets.description: The number of packets received at the indicated bdgPort that were less than the IEEE 802.3 minimum Ethernet frame size of 64 bytes.

bdgPortOversizePackets.name: bdgPortOversizePackets
bdgPortOversizePackets.description: The number of packets received at the indicated port that were greater than the IEEE 802.3 maximum Ethernet frame size of 1518 bytes.

bdgPortFrFilt.name: bdgPortFrFilt
bdgPortFrFilt.description: The number of frames received at the indicated port that were filtered by the bridge.

acqTotalEntries.name: acqTotalEntries
acqTotalEntries.description: The total number of entries in the acquired database.
